    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 8,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 9,
      "text": "SUBJECT: FLYING DISCS",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 10,
      "text": "[REDACTED] Informant b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 11,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 12,
      "text": "Reference is made to your letter dated August 11, 1947 in the above captioned",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 13,
      "text": "matter.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 14,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 15,
      "text": "[REDACTED], McHenry County, Woodstock, Illinois, advised that he had",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 16,
      "text": "received no reports of flying discs in the community of Lily Lake, Illinois.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 17,
      "text": "He further stated that he had no record or knowledge of [REDACTED] of b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 18,
      "text": "Lily Lake.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 19,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 20,
      "text": "[REDACTED], Lily Lake, Illinois, advised that he was per-",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 21,
      "text": "sonally acquainted with [REDACTED] whom he described as a successful",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 22,
      "text": "writer of mystery stories. He said he had no information to the effect that b7c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 23,
      "text": "SHAVER was mentally unsound and he believed him to be a substantial citizen.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 24,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 25,
      "text": "[REDACTED] advised she had sold property to",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 26,
      "text": "[REDACTED] on two occasions and was well acquainted with [REDACTED] and his wife. b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 27,
      "text": "She knew of no derogatory information concerning him.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 28,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 29,
      "text": "[REDACTED] was interviewed at Lily Lake, Illinois and advised that",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 30,
      "text": "he was the featured writer of mystery stories for [REDACTED] magazine, which",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 31,
      "text": "magazine is edited by [REDACTED] b7c",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 32,
      "text": "Chicago, Illinois. [REDACTED] at the outset stated that PALMER had told him the",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 33,
      "text": "FBI would contact him regarding flying discs.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 34,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 35,
      "text": "[REDACTED] indicated that the telegram received by the War Department, referre.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 36,
      "text": "to in referenced letter, was probably sent by one of his readers, unknown to",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 37,
      "text": "him. He said that he wrote mystery stories based on his firm conviction that",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 38,
      "text": "under the earth are various caverns formerly inhabited by a super race, who",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 39,
      "text": "have since fled to other planets. This region of caverns he calls Lemuria. b7c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 40,
      "text": "He stated he believes there is valuable machinery and other resources in these",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 41,
      "text": "caverns. He therefore explained flying discs, which he calls \"space ships\",",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 42,
      "text": "as the mode of travel of the Lemurians coming from other planets to reclaim",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 43,
      "text": "the valuable machinery. [REDACTED] indicated that his theories had aroused a",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 44,
      "text": "wide following among readers of [REDACTED] magazine.",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 45,
      "status": "blank"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 46,
      "text": "[REDACTED] exhibited an article from an edition of the \"Chicago Times\" for Sunday,",
      "status": "permanent_unresolved",
      "unresolvedReason": "other_documented"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 47,
      "text": "August 3, 1947. The article stated that on June 24, 1947, on Murray Island,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 48,
      "text": "off the Washington Coast, there had occurred a mysterious explosion which was b7c",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 49,
      "text": "believed to have been caused by a guided missile or rocket. It further stated",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 50,
      "text": "that the date of the explosion was the same date on which one KENNETH ARNOLD,",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
    {
      "lineNumber": 51,
      "text": "a private pilot, sighted the first flying disc at Boise, Idaho.",
      "status": "image_matched"
    },
